The ORF lengths were identical for the pol, E, M, N and 7b genes of FRSCV MSU-1 and FRECV MSU-2. The 4.35 kb S sequence of FRECV MSU-2 is 24 nucleotides shorter, observed as a deletion of 8 amino acid residues in a pairwise comparison of predicted protein sequences (Fig. 3
). ORF 3 of FRSCV MSU-1 is only 252 bases (83 amino acids) long compared to 744 bases (247 amino acids) in FRECV MSU-2. In the ORF 3 sequence alignment in Fig. 4
, it can be observed that the ATG start codon at position 9, found in the enteric strain, has been replaced with a GTG in the systemic strain, resulting in a delayed start site further downstream at nucleotide position 311 for FRSCV MSU-1. In addition, the systemic strain has a 193-base deletion that corresponds to positions 228–420 within the intact ORF 3 gene of FRECV MSU-2.
